"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s15_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0c240b",
"children":[
"Hemoglobin is a tetrameric molecule. The two α-globin chains and two β-globin chains are linked to heme (iron and protoporphyrin) and reversibly bind one molecule of oxygen. The thalassemic syndromes result from defects in synthesis of α or β chains and lead to ineffective erythropoiesis and hemolysis. Patients with α-thalassemia or β-thalassemia have microcytosis and target cells on the peripheral blood smear and may have splenomegaly."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_s15_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fbc79c",
"children":[
"β-Thalassemia is most common among persons from the Mediterranean, Southeast Asia, India, and Pakistan. β-Thalassemia results from several abnormalities in the β-gene complex. Decreased β-chain synthesis leads to impaired production of hemoglobin A (α",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"β",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
") and resultant increased synthesis of hemoglobin A",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" (α",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"δ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
") and/or hemoglobin F (α",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"γ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
")."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_s15_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c6d359",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"β-Thalassemia trait and α-thalassemia trait are commonly confused with iron deficiency anemia."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_s15_inline_t3"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fe9885",
"children":[
"β-Thalassemia can be associated with iron overload even in the absence of transfusion therapy."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s15_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dcaa92",
"children":[
"Thalassemia treatment varies with the type of disease:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"57294b",
"children":[
"folate supplementation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5617b4",
"children":[
"no iron replacement unless iron deficiency is documented"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bd47bb",
"children":[
"genetic counseling"
]
},
" "
]
},
