{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s15_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e3120f",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"An asymptomatic 18-year-old man has a hemoglobin concentration of 13 g/dL, an ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"mean corpuscular volume",
"children":[
"MCV"
]
},
" of 64 fL, and a reticulocyte count of 4% of erythrocytes."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a1e9f5",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"The diagnosis is β-thalassemia or α-thalassemia trait. For management, select serum ferritin measurement and hemoglobin electrophoresis."
]
}
]
}
]
},
